      • getPortForURI

        public static int getPortForURI(SocketAddress socketAddress,
                                int defaultPort)
        Get the port number for the given socket address. If the port number matches the given default port, then -1 is returned to allow the URI to use the default value.
        Parameters:
        socketAddress - the destination socket address
        defaultPort - the default port number for the URI scheme, or -1 if there is none or it is unknown
        Returns:
        the URI port number

      • getDestinationInetAddress

        public static InetAddress getDestinationInetAddress(URI uri)
                                             throws UnknownHostException
        Get an Internet address for a URI destination, resolving the host name if necessary.
        Parameters:
        uri - the destination URI
        Returns:
        the socket address, or null if no authority is present in the URI
        Throws:
        UnknownHostException - if the URI host was existent but could not be resolved to a valid address

      • getDestinationInetSocketAddress

        public static InetSocketAddress getDestinationInetSocketAddress(URI uri,
                                                                int defaultPort)
        Get a socket address for a URI destination, resolving the host name if necessary. If the host name could not be resolved, an unresolved address is returned.
        Parameters:
        uri - the destination URI
        defaultPort - the default port number for the URI scheme, or -1 if there is none or it is unknown
        Returns:
        the socket address, or null if no authority is present in the URI or no port number could be determined
